ğŸ” 1. Linux File & Folder Permissions
ğŸ§® Numeric Permission Codes
Symbol	Code	Meaning
r	4	Read
w	2	Write
x	1	Execute

ğŸ” Real Example

-rw-r--r-- 1 ec2-user ec2-user  myfile.txt
Owner â†’ Read & Write (rw-)

Group â†’ Read only (r--)

Others â†’ Read only (r--)

ğŸ”§ Useful Commands

chmod o+w file.txt        # Give write to others
chmod o-r file.txt        # Remove read from others
chmod ugo+rwx file.txt    # Give all access to everyone
chmod 740 file.txt        # u: read/write/execute, g: read, o: no access

ğŸ§‘â€ğŸš€ 2. SSH Key-Based Login
SSH is how you log into cloud servers without typing passwords like a noob.

ğŸš€ Steps to Setup:
mkdir ~/.ssh
chown kalyan:kalyan ~/.ssh
touch ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
chmod 700 ~/.ssh

ğŸ”‘ Login Using:
